data.title: Very special place to take your special one.
data.text: Excellent food excellent service. Can't be beat in Daytona. Atmosphere cozy and clean. Very enjoyable and friendly.

data.title: 10 year Anniversary
data.text: I want to start off by saying I expected the nicest restaurant in Daytona Beach based off the reviews I read in advance. It truly was an amazing experience as well as romantic. The conversations were loud, but that didn't bother me a bit. My wife and I arrived 15 minutes prior to our 1830 reservation and were seated immediately in this quaint historical house owned by president Warren G. Harding. Our waiter Joseph was a true professional and Id like to focus first on his service. He was passionate about his job as a server and ensuring a wonderful experience. He was a true gentleman to both my wife and I, and though the place filled up fast, ill quote my wife. "He made us feel as if we were the only two he was serving." He was very intelligent about the menu as if we were hearing it from the chef. I took his recommendations on both the main course and the desert and they were both to die for. The food exceeded our expectation in every way. From presentation, to the timing, to the way that every bite engaged another part of the pallet revealing hints of fresh herbs and spices in the sauces as well as the perfection of the homemade pasta. The tomatoes in the Rigatoni a la Checca (I believe the dish was called) were stewed to a perfection I didn't know was possible. Cooked anymore they'd fall apart, any less and they wouldn't nail that amazing flavor. The veal shank (which was the special) was cooked in an equally delectable way. I believe Id need a degree to describe the flavors! The portions were spot on. Just enough food to fill you up, but not too much to where I felt too full enjoy every bite. Lastly, the desert was Sweet and delicious. Tiramisu served at the perfect temperature consistency and a chocolate tart that had a strong natural cocoa flavor with enough sugar to sweeten it to perfection paired with an authentic Italian Expresso. The attire is business casual, and It would be nice if everyone would stick to that. A few gentleman came underdressed in work t-shirts which was inappropriate for this dining experience. My wife and I will be back. Cell phones are discouraged to be used, but I snuck a few pictures of this amazing Itallian cuisine to share! Thank you The Cellar and Joseph for making my 10th Anniversary a memorable one!

data.title: Experience You Won't Forget
data.text: My husband took me to this phenomenal restaurant for our 10 year anniversary. Our waiter, Joesph, was amazing to say the least. He knew the menu front and back. No matter how busy he seemed when he was at your table serving you, you weren't rushed at all. He made you feel like you were the only table in the place. Joesph took the time to explain any questions on the menu you may have had, was very attentive to ensure that your experience met your needs and expectations. Would highly recommend to anyone and everyone that is in or traveling to the Daytona area.

data.title: Worth the wait... but we did have to wait
data.text: The food was excellent . The wine choices under Lena's guidance were wonderful . However the time frame for the courses was much too long.

data.title: Amazing Food and Splendid Atmosphere
data.text:
The basement of a house is not usually the place I'd go for dinner, but the atmosphere here is like stepping into another country.  Very eloquent and polished.   The staff look like they know what they are doing and they were polite and effective.  
I never had beets or arugula, both of which I tried and found that I should now add these to my list of foods to enjoy.  
Thank you for expanding my insight and my palate.  It was a joy eating here.

data.title: Outstanding
data.text: Outstanding food and service. Our waiter Chris was attentive without hovering. Made some excellent suggestions.

data.title: Not just the best in Daytona, it rivals best anywhere
data.text: The Cellar was referred to us by the innkeeper at Coquina Inn, and we were impressed. There was such variety and originality in the menu, atmosphere of class and refinement, wine list shows in-depth knowledge and experience, and desserts to die for.

data.title: Best Italian Restaurant in Volusia County
data.text: We visit The Cellar for every special occasion, birthdays, anniversaries, full moons, etc. We're from the North and the Cellar is the only restaurant we've found in the area that meets the standards of some of the finest Italian restaurants in NY City.

data.title: Very good but...
data.text:
The staff are super attentive without being too intrusive.
The menu is quite expansive...
If you are wanting appetizer, Primi Piatti, Secundi Piatti and desert...I hope that you bring your appetite.
Portion sizes whilst not big for USA are still big compared to European plates and getting through the full menu required more room than I had available.
The wine list is very good.
The food itself was good...not outstanding.
Would I visit again...probably not.
Is it worth going if you have not been, yes.

data.title: Great place for a romantic meal
data.text: Always a great and attentive staff and the food is just wonderful.  They have a great selection of wine which they would be glad to pair with your meal.

data.title: Been a long time since we have been there; but it was excellent - want to go back
data.text: It has been a long time since we have been there; but it was excellent and casually elegant. We really want to go back soon.

data.title: Outstanding!
data.text: My husband and I visit Daytona Beach and The Cellar a couple of times a year, and we are never disappointed.  Our visit yesterday evening was excellent!  From the extensive wine list to the special tuna appetizer, to the fresh pasta with crab meat to the homemade strudel ... everything was exquisite....perfect.

data.title: Yum!!!
data.text: What a great dinner!  The food was amazing!  Although it was a little pricey it was well worth it!!!  The service was spectacular!  The ambiance was nice. Make sure you look around at the pictures of President Harding and his wife. The stain glass was gorgeous!  Not a place I would choose to take children.

data.title: Disappointing dinner at Cellar
data.text: I read the online reviews and thought this place sounded fantastic.  However, my steak was undercooked, the marlin was overcooked, and the rest was nothing to write home about.    I expect these problems for a $20 meal, not at these prices.

data.title: You feel like royalty
data.text:
Excellent experience and not overpriced when considering the service and ambiance, and most important the food! 
There is a dress code however!

data.title: Wow!
data.text:
So, good food really is available in Daytona! We absolutely love this place! We all wished we were dressed a little nicer when we came here, but everyone was very friendly and professional. We did not feel awkward, but we will bring some better clothes next trip! 
The food was amazing. The Osso Bucco was incredible-this is the winning order. The filet mignon was also very good, pappardelle with sausage was tasty and the snapper in lobster sauce was good, but definitely the Osso Bucco is the best. Also loved the red pepper appetizer. Desserts were not the high point and probably will not try one again, but it's my least favorite part of a meal, so no great loss. 
It's a little pricey, but, so worth it!

data.title: consistantly great
data.text: Never been disappointed, one of the best.Food & Service always been top notch. Creative & diverse in all dishes. Great wine selection.

data.title: Lovely environment for a delicious dinner!
data.text: Six friends had dinner together at The Cellar recently. The food of all was delicious, perfectly prepared , served well , and a good time was had by all. We recommend The Cellar wholeheartedly.

data.title: Intimate setting with a great wine list
data.text: This was a gem of a recommendation from a friend in FL. From the moment we walked in, to the second we left, we were made to feel welcomed and special. We had a lovely server, who had the most impeccable manners. We started with a bottle of white wine and a nightly special appetizer of grilled octopus. Delicious! For dinner we ordered the Rigatoni con Gamberi e Asperagi and Osso Buco D'Angelo con Risotto alle Verdure.  Each dish was presented beautifully and tasted even better. The pasta was homemade, cooked al dente, in a light sauce with shaved asparagus and shrimp. The lamb Osso Buco was tender and had a depth of flavor like none other. This is a must go to if you are ever in the area.  Bravo!!!

data.title: The best in Daytona Beach
data.text: We live in the area but have not eaten here in some time.  Decided to revisit after talking with friends who still highly recommended the restaurant.  The 4 of us were not disappointed.  Everything from the wine to the dessert was exquisite.  The service was properly paced and attentive.  The cost of the meal was expensive, for Daytona, but you definitely get what you pay for.  Reservations are a must and since the restaurant is fairly small must be made well ahead Make sure to try one of the veal dishes and you will not be disapppointed.  We will return again.
